images:
A highly detailed, technical blueprint-style developer infographic poster on the theme of "ORCHESTRATOR PATTERN IN CODE".
Overall Theme: High-tech dark mode developer dashboard, cybersecurity blueprint, with sharp glowing lines and neat borders.
Colors: Deep dark navy background with glowing neon blue, electric cyan, warning red, and success green highlights.

Header:
- A prominent top-center glowing blue header: "ORCHESTRATOR PATTERN IN CODE".
- Below it, a clean subtitle: "How to Implement Centralized Control with Typed Agent Contracts" with a small Salesforce logo on the top-left and an "APEX BEST PRACTICES" badge on the top-right.

Section 1: "WHY IT MATTERS" (Top Row, 3 Horizontal Cards)
- "Central State" with a target icon, "Confidence Gates" with a filter icon, "Full Audit Log" with a shield icon

Section 2: "THE COST" (Middle Row, Side-by-Side Comparison)
- Left Box (Red Theme): "GROUP CHAT — Agents Call Each Other Freely". Shows a red status pill "DANGER — ANTI-PATTERN".
- Right Box (Green Theme): "ORCHESTRATOR — State Owned in One Place". Shows a green status pill "SUCCESS — BEST PRACTICE".

Section 3: "CODE PATTERNS" (Main Center)
- Left Column (Bad Code in Red Border):
  - Heading: "// BAD"
  - Code block:
    // Group chat: agents message each other freely
const intake = new IntakeAgent()
const response = await intake.run(context)
// intake randomly messages KnowledgeAgent
// KnowledgeAgent messages EntitlementAgent
// State is scattered. Who owns the decision?
- Right Column (Good Code in Green Border):
  - Heading: "// GOOD"
  - Code block:
    // Orchestrator owns all state transitions
const intake = await runWithTimeout(
  agents.intake, context, 8000)
if (intake.confidence < 0.75) {
  return { status: 'HUMAN_REVIEW', auditLog }
}
const entitlement = await runWithTimeout(
  agents.entitlement, context, 8000)

Section 4: "DEVELOPER PROFILE & CHECKLIST" (Bottom Row)
- Left Side: A 3D Pixar-style cartoon avatar portrait of a dark-skinned South Asian male with a full thick black beard, shoulder-length wavy dark hair pulled up into a messy top bun, warm friendly smile showing teeth, wearing a grey crew-neck sweatshirt with the word "MAGNETIC" on it, set against a warm orange bokeh background. The avatar is labeled "Bennie Joseph | Salesforce Architect". Next to it is a quote bubble: "Architecting intuitive systems, engineering scalable solutions."
- Right Side: A checklist with points: "Orchestrator owns all workflow state — no inter-agent messaging", "Every agent: typed input → typed output + confidence score", "Confidence gate fires before each downstream agent step", "MAX_TURNS enforced — workflow cannot loop indefinitely", "Full AgentResult array in audit log before any DML".
- Footer: A thin bar with icons for "Multi-Agent", "TypeScript", "Agentforce 2.0", "Audit Trail" and the text "CODE SMART. AUTOMATE FASTER. DELIVER EXCELLENCE."

Style Details: Super high resolution, technical drawing grid, razor-sharp white and neon text, crisp layout, developer IDE aesthetic, flat vector graphics with subtle glow, highly legible monospace font for code blocks, professional presentation.
